dict.string: The bounciness of the physics body. This property is used to determine how much energy the physics body loses when it bounces off another object. The property must be a value between 0.0 and 1.0.
The vertical value of the force of gravity in a pair of coordinates
The horizontal value of the force of gravity in a pair of coordinates
Coordinates are a set of values that show an exact position.
the force of attraction between all masses in the universe; especially the attraction of the earth's mass for bodies near its surface
